Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 15:17:42 2026 -0400

    feat(forms)(form-engine): FormDefinition schema + closed kind-set + tests

    Replace the page-level-copy-only placeholder FormDefinition (Branch 5.1) with
    the structural field-graph schema in app/lib/forms/definition.ts (ADR 0007,
    CONTEXT ┬¦Form definition). A FormDefinition is data ŌĆö the JSON at
    forms/<form>.json ŌĆö describing a form's field graph, variants, and cross-field
    rules; the generic renderer/decoder (6.2+) read it.

    Closed FieldKind set (make-impossible-states-unrepresentable): a tagged union
    over exactly the eight kinds the three forms use ŌĆö requiredText, optionalText,
    email, url, literal, checkboxBoolean, arrayOfLiteral, nestedGroup (recursive via
    Schema.suspend). Plus a discriminated FormVariantSet (registration's
    attendee/exhibitor) and a closed CrossFieldRule set (requiredWhenEquals).

    Boundary brands (boundary-discipline, derive-dont-sync):
    - MessageKey validates every failure message against the live translations
      object, so a definition can never reference an error key that renders blank.
    - FieldName / OptionValue are constrained tokens safe to interpolate into a
      form-data path / radio value.
    - unique field names; non-empty option lists; >=2 variants.

    Migrate callers, then delete the placeholder (migrate-callers-then-delete,
    subtract-before-you-add): defaults.ts, registry.ts, and the content/draft-editor
    tests now import FormDefinition from lib/forms/definition; the form defaults
    carry an empty fields graph until each form's graph is authored (6.3-6.5); the
    placeholder is removed from content/pages/schema.ts and its placeholder tests
    move to forms/definition.test.ts.

    Tests: full round-trip exercising every kind + a variant + a rule; closed
    kind-set (unknown _tag rejected); off-list MessageKey, dotted FieldName,
    whitespace OptionValue, empty option list, duplicate names, one-member variant
    set, blank-locale label, unknown rule kind ŌĆö all hard decode errors.

